  "source_notes": "Mihaela Dicu quotes birth certificate, a copy of which she sent via e-mail to PT with the following notes: .Nicolae Ceausescu February 5 (January 23 Julian, OS), 12:00 Bucharest Time (-1h44'24\") 1918, Scornicesti, Romania (44°34'12\"N, 24°33'0\"E) See birth document in attach. The birth hour was provided by the father, and I think it may be not very exact. The child was born on January 23, at home, and the birth document was laid down on January 26.I was surprise to see that Ceausescu is born on 23, because he used to celebrate his anniversary on 26. But we have the official paper...Romania adopted the Gregorian calendar in 1919, so we must add 13 days to obtain the real data, and that is February 5.\"\\nThe original ADB entry gave January 26, 1918, 12:00, Bucuresti Romania and was rated X, (date, no time) with the following source notes:  LMR quotes Welcome to the Planet Earth for the date. Taeger Lexikon quotes the Weiss Journal for a speculative 8:00 PM.\\n",
